  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-6">
          Enterprise-Grade Multi-Tenancy
        </h2>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            Multi-tenant architecture provides complete data isolation for
            enterprise security requirements. Each organization operates on
            dedicated database instance with zero possibility of data crossover
            between tenants. This isolation ensures that Company A's scheduling
            data, user information, and business details remain completely
            separate from Company B's data. Unlike shared database architectures
            where logical separation creates potential security vulnerabilities,
            CalendHub's isolated database approach provides physical separation
            that meets strictest enterprise security standards.
          </p>

          <p>
            Custom subdomain routing creates professional branded experience for
            each organization. When Company A's employees access
            company.calendhub.com, they connect directly to Company A's isolated
            instance with Company A's branding, settings, and data. This
            dedicated routing eliminates confusion about which organizational
            context users are operating in and creates seamless branded
            experience. Subdomain architecture also enables custom SSL
            certificates, branded login pages, and organization-specific
            configurations that maintain professional appearance throughout
            scheduling workflows.
          </p>

          <p>
            Automatic scaling handles growing tenant base without performance
            degradation. As you add new organizational customers, CalendHub
            provisions additional isolated database instances automatically.
            Each new tenant receives dedicated resources that ensure consistent
            performance regardless of overall platform size. This scalable
            architecture prevents the "noisy neighbor" problem where one
            high-volume tenant impacts performance for others. Your scheduling
            platform grows with your customer base while maintaining
            enterprise-grade performance and reliability for every organization.
          </p>

          <p>
            Compliance-ready architecture meets regulatory requirements for data
            handling and privacy. Isolated databases enable GDPR compliance
            through clear data boundaries and straightforward deletion
            processes. SOC 2 compliance benefits from physical data separation
            and comprehensive audit logging at tenant level. HIPAA-compliant
            healthcare organizations can use CalendHub knowing that protected
            health information remains isolated from other tenants. This
            compliance-focused architecture reduces legal risk and enables
            serving regulated industries with confidence.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
