            <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-4">
              Database-Per-Tenant Architecture with Dynamic Provisioning
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              CalendHub implements true database isolation where each tenant
              receives dedicated PostgreSQL instance rather than sharing tables
              with row-level security. This physical separation eliminates
              entire categories of data leakage vulnerabilities that plague
              shared database architectures. When new organization signs up,
              provisioning system automatically creates isolated database,
              configures replication for high availability, and sets up
              tenant-specific backup schedules. Custom subdomain routing uses
              middleware that examines incoming request domain, identifies
              target tenant, and establishes connection to correct database
              instance. This architecture enables seamless tenant onboarding
              while maintaining absolute data isolation that satisfies
